Arrays:-

* Collection of similar kind of data in a continous allocation.
  *   in C and C++ we have pointers defiantly elements will be stored in continious format.
* In java we don’t have pointers then there is a chance of elements might stored in random places.
* Syntax:-
* Data type []and array name.
* Primitive and non primitive 
* Primitive data type :  primitive data type can’t be splited.
* Ex- int, float,char . 


* Non primitive :- non primitive data can’t be divided 
* Ex- string, array,All the objects that are created by users.
