Camel case and Snake case:- 
To string the size of an array and initialising the values later;
To string can accept only one argument and that too array.

In java it preferred to use camel case to write production level code.
We can us array values for simple for loops.
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int [] arr = {10,11,12,13};
        
        for (int i : arr){
            System.out.print(i + " ");
        }
        

    }
}
In for each loop we don’t need index values. 
Two strings is an inbuilt method to print an array.
Array having fixed size if we declare an array size it can’t be changed.
With the help of new keyword actual object will be created in the heap memory for that particular datatype and size.
if the array type is  int all the default values are zero.




